author: Jessica Chia For Dailymail.Com
title: One missing and two others injured in pipeline explosion | Daily Mail Online
text: Pipeline explosion causing 40ft 'blow torch' fire leaves one missing and two injured in Louisiana - and may take DAYS to burn out Six employees were cleaning a pipeline at the Paradis Pipeline Station on Thursday An explosion broke out, resulting in a massive fire that continues to burn Two were hospitalized and helicopters will aid in search for missing employee It remains unclear whether a valve or gasket failed; the pipeline source has been turned off and officials are waiting for the fire to burn out Sixty homes were evacuated and highways were being diverted Published: 14:47 GMT, 10 February 2017 | Updated: 15:42 GMT, 10 February 2017 157 shares
